threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factors were that it matches yara rules with files that have detections and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET INFO Dotted Quad Host DOC Request
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert http $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET any (msg:"ET INFO Dotted Quad Host DOC Request"; flow:established,from_client; flowbits:isset,http.dottedquadhost; flowbits:set,http.dottedquadhost.doc; flowbits:unset,http.dottedquadhost; http.request_line; content:".doc HTTP/1."; nocase; fast_pattern; classtype:bad-unknown; sid:2027251; rev:4; metadata:attack_target Client_Endpoint, created_at 2019_04_23, deployment Perimeter, former_category INFO, performance_impact Significant, signature_severity Minor, updated_at 2020_04_08;)

alert dns $HOME_NET any -> any any (msg:"ET DNS Query for .to TLD"; dns.query; content:".to"; endswith; fast_pattern; classtype:bad-unknown; sid:2027757; rev:5; metadata:affected_product Any, attack_target Client_Endpoint, created_at 2019_07_26, deployment Perimeter, former_category DNS, signature_severity Minor, updated_at 2020_09_17;)

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET INFO Observed ZeroSSL SSL/TLS Certificate
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tls $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"ET INFO Observed ZeroSSL SSL/TLS Certificate"; flow:from_server,established; tls.cert_issuer; content:"ZeroSSL"; classtype:bad-unknown; sid:2031231; rev:1; metadata:created_at 2020_11_23, updated_at 2020_11_23;)

alert tcp $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET 443 ( msg:"POLICY-OTHER SSLv3 Client Hello attempt"; flow:to_server,established; ssl_state:client_hello; ssl_version:sslv3; content:"|16 03 00|",depth 3; service:ssl; reference:cve,2002-1623; reference:cve,2013-2566; classtype:policy-violation; sid:41807; rev:3; )

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp any any -> any $HTTP_PORTS ( msg:"POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt"; flow:to_server,established; http_header; content:"Host:",fast_pattern,nocase; pcre:"/^Host\x3a\s*(?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\s*:?\s*\d*\s*$/smi"; service:http; reference:url,www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec15.html; classtype:policy-violation; sid:50447; rev:1; )
